Lagos – Nigerian singer, Azeez Fashola popularly known as Naira Marley, was in court earlier today to continue his criminal trial. Marley appeared at a Federal High Court in Lagos for his trial, However, the court adjourned the alleged card fraud trial of the musician who is facing card fraud charges.Justice Nicholas Oweibo made the decision so as to allow the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission counsel Mr Rotimi Oyedepo and Fashola’s counsel Mr Olalekan Ojo SAN to respond to two motions. A video has now emerged showing Naira Marley in court. Watch video below: Alleged Fraud: #NairaMarley back in court, today, in #LagosState; case adjourned till tomorrow A post shared by  Instablog9ja (@instablog9ja) on Oct 22, 2019 at 3:54am PDT Source